.TH verilog 9
.XI verilog - "Verilog hardware description language"
.XI v - "Verilog hardware description language"
.SH SYNOPSIS
Verilog \- Verilog hardware description language
.SH FILES
.na
.B hkverilg.emf
\- Verilog hardware description language hook definition
.ad
.SH EXTENSIONS
.na
\fB.v\fR \- Verilog file
.ad
.SH DESCRIPTION
The  \fBVerilog\fR  file type template  provides  simple  highlighting  of the
Verilog  hardware  description  language.  \fB.v\fR  files  are  automatically
recognized as Verilog files. For the documentation of the V programming language look at
.Ht vlang 9 .
.IP \fBHilighting\fR
The  hilighting  features  allow  commands,  variables  and  operators  of the
language to be differentiated and rendered in different colors.
.IP \fBComments\fR
Comments  may be formatted  using  \fC\*eo\fR,  which  reformats  the comments
according  to  the  current  fill  paragraph.
.IP "\fBShort Cuts\fR"
The short cut keys used within the buffer are:-
.IP
\fB\*eh\fR \- Key binding help information.
.br
\fB\*cc \*cc\fR \- Comment out the current line.
.br
\fB\*cc \*cd\fR \- Uncomment the current line.
.br
\fB\*cc \*ce\fR \- Comment to the end of the line with hash (#).
.br
\fB\*cc \*co\fR \- Format a comment
